user_query:
I need a make–buy–partner strategy for our Smart Thermostat BU. Please read both input/business_activities.csv and input/company_context.json, then produce a comprehensive partnering map and decisions aligned to our stated priorities and constraints.

Deliverables:
1) Write a machine-checkable partnering map to output/partnering_map.json using the exact schema below.

JSON schema (required top-level keys and structures):
{
  "business_unit": string,
  "activity_analysis": [
    {"activity": string, "current_approach": "In-house"|"Outsource"|"Partnership"|"Transactional", "partner_type": string, "importance": "High"|"Medium"|"Low", "alternatives": [string, ...], "recommended_relationship": "Full Integration"|"Joint Venture"|"Strategic Alliance"|"Long-term Contract"|"Transactional"|"Do-Yourself"}
  ],
  "relationship_matrix": [
    {"partner": string, "duration": string, "dependency": "High"|"Medium"|"Low", "switching_cost": "High"|"Medium"|"Low", "strategic_fit": "Green"|"Yellow"|"Red"}
  ],
  "strategic_decisions": {
    "<Activity name from CSV>": {"current_approach": string, "recommended_action": "Keep"|"Change", "rationale": string, "timeline": string}
  },
  "capabilities_gap_analysis": [
    {"capability": string, "internal": "Strong"|"Medium"|"Weak", "available_via_partner": "Strong"|"Medium"|"Weak", "gap": "High"|"Medium"|"Low", "priority": string}
  ],
  "risk_assessment": [
    {"risk": string, "partner": string, "impact": "High"|"Medium"|"Low", "mitigation": string}
  ],
  "next_steps": [
    {"step": number, "action": string, "owner": string, "deadline": string}
  ],
  "governance": {"decision_authority": string, "review_process": string},
  "portfolio_strategy": {
    "partnership_philosophy": string,
    "relationship_types_breakdown": {"Full Integration": number, "Joint Venture": number, "Strategic Alliance": number, "Long-term Contract": number, "Transactional": number, "Do-Yourself": number}
  },
  "value_capture": {
    "items": [
      {"relationship_type": "In-house"|"Outsource"|"Partnership", "value_created": number, "cost": number, "net_benefit": number}
    ],
    "total_value": number
  },
  "exit_criteria": [
    {"relationship": string, "when_to_consider_exit": string, "triggers": string}
  ],
  "monitoring": [
    {"metric": "Partner performance", "frequency": string, "owner": string, "status": "Green"|"Yellow"|"Red"},
    {"metric": "Cost of outsourced activities", "frequency": string, "owner": string, "status": "Green"|"Yellow"|"Red"}
  ]
}

Implementation notes and constraints:
- Use only the data from input/business_activities.csv and input/company_context.json. Map every Activity from the CSV into activity_analysis and create one strategic_decisions entry per Activity.
- In relationship_matrix, include every unique partner found in the CSV CurrentPartner(s) field (split by ';'). Assign dependency, switching_cost, duration, and strategic_fit.
- portfolio_strategy.relationship_types_breakdown must sum exactly to the total number of activities in the CSV.
- monitoring must include exactly the two metrics listed above (you may add additional metrics only if you include them in addition to these two, but these two must be present as specified).
- Align recommendations and rationales with the context file's strategic_priorities, risk_appetite, governance, and constraints. Keep all file paths relative and write only to output/.

2) Optionally, write a human-readable summary to output/partnering_map.md, but the JSON will be the primary artifact for validation.
